    <h2 id="why-vitamin-e">Why Over 90% of Americans Are Not Getting Enough Vitamin E</h2>

    <p>Vitamin E is a fat-soluble antioxidant that protects every cell membrane in your body from oxidative damage. It neutralizes free radicals generated by UV exposure, air pollution, cigarette smoke, and normal metabolic processes. It enhances immune function by supporting T-cell proliferation and natural killer cell activity. It protects LDL cholesterol from oxidation — a key early step in atherosclerosis. And it maintains the integrity of the skin lipid barrier, the outermost defense against environmental damage and transepidermal water loss.</p>

